Picking a pizza place to go to in Chicago is always a hassle, but I had a friend who raved about Bonci so I really wanted to visit. Bonci did not disappoint! There are so many things that make this place very worth your time and money.  The dough and crust of their Roman-style pizzas are super good and will remind you of focaccia with its airy texture. I really enjoyed the fried onion and sausage and mushroom pizzas but there are tons of flavors to choose from. You get to pick how large of a slice you'd like cut for you (so smaller slices = more flavors) and they're priced by the pound, so I'd say around 1lb is good for a meal. On that note, there are lots of vegan and vegetarian options! I'm not either myself but it's great knowing this is a place I can bring friends who are.  The service is very fast and the space, while small, is very clean. Since all the tables are high-top bar tables, Bonci is a great place to come with a couple of friends or for a quick lunch, but probably not any large parties.
